results.name: Number of asymmetric 2,3 cacti (triangular cacti with bridges).
link: Andrew Howroyd, Table of n, a(n) for n = 1..500
Index entries for sequences related to cacti
program: b(n)={my(p=O(x)); for(n=1, n, p=x+x^2*(Ser(WeighT(Vec(p + (p^2 - subst(p,x,x^2))/2))))); p}
seq(n)={my(p=b(n)); Vec(p - p^2/2 - p^3/3 - subst(p, x, x^2)/2 + subst(p, x, x^3)/3)} \\ _Andrew Howroyd_, Aug 30 2018
